          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>What is the 60-Day Price Match Guarantee?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>We guarantee price protection for orders placed during Heybike 4th Anniversary Sale. If you find a lower price on the exact same product within 60 days of your purchase on Heybike official website, simply reach out to our customer service team with proof of the lower price. Our team will verify the information, and issue a refund for the price difference depending on the specific situation.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_jJgxhe": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Does my Heybike ebike come pre-assembled?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Your ebike will arrive partially assembled. There are just a few pieces to put into place once you take the bike out of the box. For unboxing and setup instructions, please follow the guides on our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLY2mr2usEhKHF8L_Qrf_jY0CFlBEmzat9\">YouTube Channel</a></p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_xA8KHi": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Can I ride Heybike ebikes on rainy days?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>You can ride in light rain and don't have to worry about damage caused by spray from wet roads and raindrops. We don't recommend riding ebikes in heavy rain or overly wet environments. As for the waterproof level, Heybike ebikes meet IPX4 standards; the motor, battery, and display meet IP64 standards.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_VKwKhX": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Can I ride an electric bike if the battery runs out? </strong>",
            "text": "<p>If your ebike runs out of battery, you can simply continue riding. The motor on the ebike only assists your pedaling (instead of doing all the work), so you can continue riding as usual without the pedal assist.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
